    5.0 out of 5 starsWrangler, Levi's, and Lee's comparison roundup
    ByHonest Abeon November 25, 2016
    Size: 33W x 29L|Color: Stonewash Mid|Verified Purchase
    I bought a pair each of regular fit, straight leg, zipper fly Levi's, Lee, and Wrangler jeans. The Levi's(505) were $40, the Lee's $32, and the Wrangler's $20. I washed all of them once, in cold water. They all fit about the same. The construction seems to be about the same too. All had 5 belt loops and reinforced the same points. They all were about the same weight denin. One difference I could find was that the Levi's had two rivets on the coin pocket while the Lee's and Wranglers had one rivet there and sewed the other side of the coin pocket into the main pocket seam. Also, the Levi's print your jean size on the outside label, while the Lee's and Wranglers do not. Both the Levi's and Lee have a double stitched external inseam on the inside of the legs and a concealed inseam on the outside of the legs. The Wranglers reversed this with the concealed inseam on the inside and a double stitched seam on the outside. The length of the inseam, compared to the advertised length, was pretty close, with the Lee's being the longest, and the Wranglers the shortest.

    Overall, I would say they all three pairs look like they will be fine over the longer term. So perhaps the price difference and your preference for brands might be the deciding factor.

    4.0 out of 5 starsPrice is Right
    ByBlake FrainaVINE VOICEon August 29, 2015
    Size: 38W x 32L|Color: Stonewash Mid|Vine Customer Review of Free Product( What's this? )
    When I met my husband years ago, he was a true blue, loyal Levi's man. But recently the price of trendy denim has skyrocketed and, while maybe not as expensive as 7 for All Mankind, Levi's has gone up enough that he abandoned them for Wranglers. After all, just about all clothing is manufactured in China anyway. You're not paying for quality, you're paying for the name. Wranglers are comparable in quality, sell for about one third the price and are readily available in myriad styles and colors at big box stores like Target.

    The Men's Authentics did not disappoint. They fit true to size/length and the waist falls at the perfect spot (not super high like "mom" jeans and not uncomfortably low-slung). He has thick thighs which can be a problem with slim fitting jeans, but the classic regular fit is just right - hugging but not squeezing his upper legs.

    Finally, the pre-faded color isn't too cheesy looking, although his preference is always a dark, unwashed indigo.

    Wranglers make great jeans for the price. These are definitely his new go-to denims.

    2.0 out of 5 starsWaist size much larger than tagged.
    Byjames andersonon November 12, 2017
    Size: 38W x 29L|Color: Light Stonewash|Verified Purchase
    These jeans label said 38'. Unfortunately they were way larger than 38'. Measured with a cloth tape measure at 40". I normally wear a 36" waist but I have gotten a little larger so I ordered 38". The other pair ( classic blue not the stone wash ) fit just right. I could have stuffed my cat into these jeans when I put them on so I gave them away hoping someone larger could use them. Next time I go to Kmart with a tape measure in hand. I suppose I could have returned them but I just gave them away and lesson learned.
    So, Sunday I went to Kmart with tape measure in hand. The Wrangler jeans tagged 38" waist actually measured 40". This is a manufacturer problem. The 36" tagged jeans actually measured 37". I bought them, washed them and they fit well. So as I said lesson learned. I guess some things should be hands on before buying. Just my 2 cents.
